    "body": "I'm not sure what you mean. This works fine for me: \r\n```\r\n#build/bin/geth --datadir /tmp/foo --password <(echo -n notsosecret) account new\r\nWARN [11-10|09:15:30] No etherbase set and no accounts found as default \r\nAddress: {3d37a6ead37e41d30f99eb87504938ddceb0f6a3}\r\n```\r\nAre you making a feature-request for  `geth --password \"mypassword\"` , or does the code above not work for you? \r\n\r\nIn case it's the former, I don't think that's a good idea, since it encourages users to feed passwords via commandline, which is a bad practice (it's saved in bash history). \r\n\r\nI'm going to close this ticket, but please reopen in case I misunderstood, and something is actually broken. ",
